00:18:15.450 --> 00:18:19.470
either amniocentesis or chorionic villi sampling, which

00:18:19.470 --> 00:18:21.160
have been, I think available for a

00:18:21.160 --> 00:18:25.090
generation now. So, those are still kind of the gold standard way to test

00:18:25.090 --> 00:18:28.190
for Down syndrome and other chromosome problems, because

00:18:28.190 --> 00:18:31.560
we have tissue from that baby. but more and

00:18:31.560 --> 00:18:33.360
more over the years, we have a lot more

00:18:33.360 --> 00:18:37.780
alternate tests that don't require evasiveness into the pregnancy.

00:18:37.780 --> 00:18:41.480
Primarily blood tests and ultrasounds that can check markers

00:18:41.480 --> 00:18:44.920
for Down syndrome, versus the amnion CVS are looking

00:18:44.920 --> 00:18:47.210
at the chromosomes and looking at the cause of

00:18:47.210 --> 00:18:50.260
