at. We actually have a term called pedigree analysis

00:22:43.255 --> 00:22:44.320
[LAUGH].

00:22:44.320 --> 00:22:46.630
and you know, it's, it's a subjective thing, but

00:22:46.630 --> 00:22:49.240
it really is looking at the pedigree. And going

00:22:49.240 --> 00:22:51.580
through kind of all the rules of what dominant

00:22:51.580 --> 00:22:54.420
inheritance looks like, what recessive inheritance looks like. So,

00:22:54.420 --> 00:22:56.930
if you see a trait that happens in a

00:22:56.930 --> 00:23:00.310
